  <!-- Security -->
  <section class="security" id="security">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="security-header fade-in">
        <div class="section-label">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          Security
        </div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Built for paranoid<br />levels of privacy.</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Zero-knowledge architecture means even we can't read your notes. Because we never see them.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="security-grid">
        <div class="security-card fade-in fade-in-delay-1">
          <div class="security-card-header">
            <div class="security-card-icon">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#30d158" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>No Central Servers</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Devices discover each other via Hyperswarm and connect directly. Data replicates over encrypted Hypercore append-only logs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="security-card fade-in fade-in-delay-2">
          <div class="security-card-header">
            <div class="security-card-icon">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#30d158" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>AES-256 Encrypted Backups</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Export your vault into a single .pnbk file secured with AES-256-GCM. The key is derived from a strong password only you know — we can't reset it, and neither can anyone else.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="security-card fade-in fade-in-delay-3">
          <div class="security-card-header">
            <div class="security-card-icon">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#30d158" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/><circle cx="12" cy="16" r="1"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Cryptographic Device Pairing</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Secure blind pairing handshake via QR code invites. Fingerprint verification prevents man-in-the-middle attacks during device linking.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="security-card fade-in fade-in-delay-4">
          <div class="security-card-header">
            <div class="security-card-icon">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#30d158" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"/><polyline points="3.27 6.96 12 12.01 20.73 6.96"/><line x1="12" y1="22.08" x2="12" y2="12"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Encrypted Media Vault</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Voice notes, document scans, and images are stored in an encrypted local vault. An isolated streaming server renders attachments without leaking unencrypted caches.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="security-card fade-in fade-in-delay-1">
          <div class="security-card-header">
            <div class="security-card-icon">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#30d158" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/><circle cx="12" cy="16" r="1"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Locked Notes Stay Locked</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Lock any note behind biometrics or a key-stretched password enforced on every paired device — the password itself is never stored. Failed attempts trigger exponential backoff, so brute force gets slower, not luckier.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="security-card fade-in fade-in-delay-2">
          <div class="security-card-header">
            <div class="security-card-icon">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#30d158" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17.94 17.94A10.07 10.07 0 0 1 12 20c-7 0-11-8-11-8a18.45 18.45 0 0 1 5.06-5.94"/><path d="M9.9 4.24A9.12 9.12 0 0 1 12 4c7 0 11 8 11 8a18.5 18.5 0 0 1-2.16 3.19"/><path d="M14.12 14.12a3 3 0 1 1-4.24-4.24"/><line x1="1" y1="1" x2="23" y2="23"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Invisible to Screenshots</h3>
          </div>
          <p>While a locked note is open, screenshots and screen capture are blocked and the app hides its content in the task switcher. What's locked on screen stays off camera.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
