  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq" id="faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-header fade-in">
        <div class="section-label">FAQ</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Questions, answered.</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          The things people ask before trusting an app with their notes.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list fade-in fade-in-delay-1">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>
            If there are no servers, how does sync actually work?
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p>Your devices find each other through the Hyperswarm distributed network and open a direct, end-to-end encrypted connection — no middleman ever stores or relays your notes. When two of your devices are online at the same time, changes replicate between them immediately. Until then, every edit waits safely on the device where you made it.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>
            What happens if I lose my phone?
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p>If you have another paired device, your notes are already on it — pair a new device to it and you're back. If it was your only device, restore from an encrypted .pnbk backup with your backup password. Without either, the data is gone: there's no server copy to recover from, by design. Export backups regularly.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>
            What if I forget my backup password?
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p>There is no reset. The backup's encryption key is derived from your password, and we never see either — that's what makes the backup safe to store anywhere. It also means nobody, including us, can unlock it for you. Treat your backup password like the keys to a safe.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>
            Do you really collect nothing?
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p>Really. No accounts, no analytics, no crash reporters, no ads, no tracking pixels. The app has no servers of ours to talk to, so there's nowhere for your data to go. Everything lives encrypted on your devices and moves only between them.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-more fade-in fade-in-delay-2">
        <a href={`${base}faq/`} class="btn-secondary">
          Browse all questions
